// Regression test (file A) for tinyc emitting wasm `static` function
// symbols with default (global) binding, causing cross-object name
// collisions in the wasm linker. Each translation unit has its own
// `static int helper(int)` with a different body — under correct
// linkage handling they must NOT shadow each other, and main() must
// call each TU's own copy.
//
// Bug history: the wasmstack-to-bin emitter wrote
//   flags = (imported ? UNDEFINED : 0)
// for every defined function symbol. Under wasm linking semantics a
// zero flag is BINDING_GLOBAL, so two .wasm.o files both defining
// `static int helper(int)` were linked as a single global symbol with
// signature mismatch, producing
//   error: type mismatch in call, expected [...] but got [...]
// when validating the linked module.

static int helper(int v) { return v + 100; }

int call_a(int v) {
    return helper(v);
}
